author: Alanna Petroff
title: Premarket: 5 things to know before the bell - Feb. 8, 2017
text:
Earnings blowout; Stocks soar; India holds steady by Alanna Petroff @AlannaPetroff February 8, 2017: 4:49 AM ET Click chart for in-depth premarket data. 1. Earnings blowout: CNN owner Time Warner ( TWX ) is reporting earnings Wednesday morning ahead of the opening bell. Investors will be looking for clues about AT&T's ( T , Tech30 ) planned purchase of the media giant, a deal that President Trump has said he opposes . 
Alaska Air ( ALK ) , Allergan ( AGN ) , GrubHub ( GRUB ) and Humana ( HUM ) are also reporting earnings in the morning. 
Tech firm Softbank ( SFTBY ) released earnings after Japanese markets closed for the day, reporting a big increase in profits. The company revealed little new information about its plan to invest billions in the United States . 
Whole Foods ( WFM ) is set to hit the earnings stage after the close. The company's shares have lost more than half their value over the past two years. 
2. Stocks near all-time highs: The Dow Jones industrial average and Nasdaq hit their highest ever levels during trading on Tuesday. Stock markets have been rallying since Trump's election. 
It's entirely possibly Wall Street will see new highs again on Wednesday.
